t hash): add/modify\\n// - Entries in base but not in target: delete (nil Entry)\\n//\\n// Both base and target should be flat maps as produced by FlattenTree.\\nfunc DiffTrees(base, target map[string]object.TreeEntry) []TreeChange {\\n    changes := make([]TreeChange, 0, len(target))\\n    \\n    // Adds and modifications\\n    for path, entry := range target {\\n        baseEntry, exists := base[path]\\n        if !exists || baseEntry.Hash != entry.Hash {\\n            e := entry // copy\\n            changes = append(changes, TreeChange{\\n                Path:  path,\\n                Entry: &object.TreeEntry{Mode: e.Mode, Hash: e.Hash},\\n            })\\n        }\\n    }\\n    \\n    // Deletions\\n    for path := range base {\\n        if _, exists := target[path]; !exists {\\n            changes = append(changes, TreeChange{Path: path, Entry: nil})\\n        }\\n    }\\n    \\n    return changes\\n}\\n```\\n\\n### Implementation Sequence\\n\\n1. **Add `DiffTrees` to `checkpoint/parse_tree.go`** -- pure function, no dependencies, easy to test.\\n\\n2. **Add tests for `DiffTrees`** in `checkpoint/parse_tree_test.go` -- test empty maps, adds only, deletes only, modifications, mixed, identical maps (no changes).\\n\\n3. **Convert `cherryPickOnto`** in `strategy/metadata_reconcile.go` (on the reconcile branch) -- replace the tip-tree flatten + `BuildTreeFromEntries` with `DiffTrees` + `ApplyTreeChanges`. Add an equivalence test similar to `tree_surgery_equiv_test.go`.\\n\\n4. **Convert `fetchAndMergeSessionsCommon`** in `strategy/push_common.go` -- replace the double-flatten-into-same-map + `BuildTreeFromEntries` with separate flattens + `DiffTrees` + `ApplyTreeChanges`. Add equivalence test.\\n\\n5. **Convert `DeleteOrphanedCheckpoints`** in `strategy/cleanup.go` -- replace flatten + prefix-delete + `BuildTreeFromEntries` with flatten (to discover paths) + build `[]TreeChange` with nil entries + `ApplyTreeChanges`. Add equivalence test.\\n\\n6. **Consider depre